-- 1. [Problem Restatement] Solve for x in the continued–fraction equation 2 + 1 / ( 1 + 1 / ( 2 + 2 / (3 + x) ) ) = 144⁄53. 2. [Key Idea] Replace the innermost piece by a single variable, simplify step-by-step, and equate the resulting rational function to 144⁄53. 3. [Proof] Let y := 2 + 2⁄(3 + x). (1) Step 1: Evaluate the outer layers. 1 + 1⁄y = (y + 1)/y ⇒ 1 / (1 + 1⁄y) = y/(y + 1). Hence the whole expression becomes 2 + y/(y + 1) = (3y + 2)/(y + 1). (2) Step 2: Force equality with 144⁄53. (3y + 2)/(y + 1) = 144/53 ⇔ 53(3y + 2) = 144(y + 1) ⇔ 159y + 106 = 144y + 144 ⇔ 15y = 38 ⇔ y = 38⁄15. (3) Step 3: Back–substitute to find x. From (1): 2 + 2/(3 + x) = 38/15 ⇒ 2/(3 + x) = 38/15 − 2 = 8/15 ⇒ 3 + x = 2·15/8 = 15/4 ⇒ x = 15/4 − 3 = 3/4. 4. [Conclusion] The only value satisfying the equation is x = 3⁄4, choice (A).
